The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 30: Cellphone operator Loop Telecom has paid a penalty of Rs 2.7 crore to the government for failing to meet the deadline for network rollout. The company has paid Rs 2.7 crore for the three circles, a company official said. Loop Telecom Ltd, which was earlier known as BPL Mobile, has licences in 21 circles but is yet to get spectrum in the New Delhi circle.                             
	 Mumbai, Dec. 30: The Reserve Bank of India has warned that sudden reversal of overseas portfolio investments that have been flooding this year could create problems for the economy. A potentially worrying feature of capital flows to India has been the dominance of portfolio flows, which are prone to sudden stops and reversals, the RBI has said.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 30: The State Bank of India plans to raise Rs 12,000 crore through bonds to fund its business growth. The central board of the bank has accorded approval for raising the capital for an aggregate amount of Rs 10,000 crore by issuing tier II bonds.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 30: The environment ministry is believed to have deferred clearances to JSW Steels Rs 25,000-crore capacity expansion proposal at Bellary and sought details of coal linkage and disaster management plans among other things.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 30: Rallis India Ltd, a subsidiary of Tata Chemicals, has completed the acquisition of a seeds research firm Metahelix Life Sciences for an all-cash deal of Rs 100 crore.
                                                                                                                          
